10 years ago. Nine year old LI Yi (WEI Dong) and his younger brother LI Er (WU Dezhou), board a train to their school. Their father, LI Hui (Sammo HUNG), is a teacher at this small town elite school of wushu (Chinese martial arts) which will be the backdrop to their growing up.   The children, who have been brought up by their grandmother since their mother's death, are excited to be starting a new life with him. 
If you like wushu/kungfu, you'll love this movie. If you have even just a little curiosity about what wushu/kungfu is, you'll love this movie.
 It is a great movie, not only because the wushu/kungfu moves are so enjoyable to watch, but also it tells about the essence, the moral of wushu/kungfu and it teaches a lesson about making choices.
 I highly recommend this movie, especially to the young adults/teens who likes wushu/kungfu.
